  "text": "Combining TRTS spectra and transients in high injection. Injection dependence of the ambipolar diffusion coefficient D am given by equation [CITATION_1] and its limits equations (7 and 8) in low/high injection. D am derived from TRTS transients (red square) and the mobility sum derived from the TRTS spectrum can be combined with equation [CITATION_2] to yield the mobility for electrons µ e and holes µ h . Horizontal bars correspond to the decay of the peak carrier concentration within the 1.8 ns TRTS transients and visualize the large uncertainty of the diffusion coefficients derived in the injection-dependent regime.",
